Name: Description
COVID-19 Hospitalizations by Neighborhoo:
Neighborhood poverty as the percentage of people earning incomes below the Federal Poverty Threshold within a ZCTA, such that: 
Low: <10% of residents in ZCTA living below the Federal Poverty Threshold 
Medium: 10% to <20% 
High: 20% to <30%
Very high: ≥30% residents living below the FPT

Rates refer to number of confirmed cases per 100,000 people in ZCTA of residence.

Name: Source Notes
COVID-19 Hospitalizations by Neighborhoo:
New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene, COVID-19 Data (2020). Retrieved from: https://github.com/nychealth/coronavirus-data

Data for COVID-19 Hospitalizations were updated weekly for the period of April 2, 2020 through April 2, 2021. These data are no longer being regularly updated. For the latest data on COVID-19, see: https://www1.nyc.gov/site/doh/covid/covid-19-data.page

Name: Notes
COVID-19 Hospitalizations by Neighborhoo:
Data are cumulative and do not represent new cases per day listed. Data are being collected in real-time and are preliminary and subject to change as COVID-19 response continues. Due to delays in reporting, recent data are incomplete. 
Decreases in hospitalization data after 10/6, are due to enhanced data cleaning processes which restricts the classification of hospitalizations due to COVID-19 only if the patient was admitted within 14 days of diagnosis date.
